Introduction

ME:I is a Japanese girl group consisting of 11 members, formed through the survival audition program Produce 101 Japan: The Girls. The final lineup was revealed on December 16, 2023. The name "ME:I" signifies "an idol loved by everyone, an idol of the future, progressing together toward a brighter tomorrow." Their debut single, "MIRAI," was released on April 17, 2024.
